President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed December 10, 2019, as Human Rights Day, December 15, 2019, as Bill of Rights Day, and the week beginning on December 8, 2019, as Human Rights Week. In his proclamation, President Trump emphasizes the importance of safeguarding individual rights and protecting them from government abuse. He highlights the significance of the Bill of Rights in guaranteeing fundamental freedoms such as religion, speech, privacy, and the right to bear arms. The President also mentions the Universal Declaration of Human Rights and the ongoing global struggle against human rights abuses. He calls upon the people of the United States to commemorate these observances with appropriate ceremonies and activities.